#compdef ztunnel
# ============================================================================
# ztunnel - Istio ambient mesh per-node proxy
#            (Rust, Apache-2.0)
#
# Author : Istio Authors
#           (Google + IBM + Solo.io + Tetrate
#            + Aviatrix engineers; the Istio
#            ambient mesh team)
# Upstream: https://github.com/istio/ztunnel
#
# `ztunnel` is Istio's per-node proxy for
# ambient service mesh - a sidecar-less
# alternative to the traditional Envoy
# sidecar deployment model. ztunnel handles
# L4 (TCP) mTLS termination + identity
# enforcement + policy + telemetry at the
# node level (one instance per Kubernetes
# node, shared across all pods on that node).
#
# Architectural role:
#   - **Layer 4 ambient proxy**: handles all
#     pod-to-pod traffic on a node via HBONE
#     (HTTP-Based Overlay Network Encapsulation;
#     mTLS-wrapped CONNECT-tunneled traffic)
#   - **In-pod CNI integration**: configured
#     via INPOD UDS to inject iptables rules
#     redirecting pod traffic through ztunnel
#   - **xDS-driven configuration**: receives
#     workload + policy configuration from
#     istiod via xDS protocol
#   - **mTLS termination**: terminates +
#     re-encrypts pod-to-pod traffic with
#     SPIFFE-based workload identity
#   - **L7 delegation**: defers L7 traffic
#     (HTTP/gRPC inspection + routing) to
#     waypoint proxies (separate Envoy
#     instances per-namespace)
#
# Distinguishing features vs Envoy sidecar mode:
#   - **No sidecar memory tax** (one ztunnel
#     per node vs one Envoy per pod = ~10-50x
#     memory reduction at scale)
#   - **Transparent injection** (no pod spec
#     mutation; CNI handles iptables)
#   - **Lower latency** (Rust + tokio-uring
#     for high-throughput L4; less hop overhead
#     than sidecar)
#   - **Rust safety** (memory-safe; eliminates
#     entire classes of CVE that historically
#     affected Envoy/C++ proxies)
#
# Use cases:
#   - Production Kubernetes service mesh at
#     scale (5,000+ pod clusters where sidecar
#     memory overhead is prohibitive)
#   - Multi-tenant SaaS where pod boundaries
#     are security boundaries (mTLS between
#     all pods enforced at node level)
#   - Greenfield service mesh deployments
#     where the sidecar model is being
#     skipped entirely
#
# Usage (deliberately minimal CLI):
#   ztunnel [proxy|version|help]
#
# Subcommands:
#   proxy (default)                - start the
#                                     ztunnel
#                                     proxy
#                                     (default
#                                     if no
#                                     command
#                                     given)
#   version                        - print
#                                     version
#                                     info
#                                     (build
#                                     hash +
#                                     build
#                                     time +
#                                     Istio
#                                     version)
#   help                           - print
#                                     commands
#                                     + version
#                                     info
#
# Configuration (via environment variables;
# no flags - ztunnel is config-via-env-only
# by design, the Kubernetes-native approach
# since envs are projected by the kubelet):
#
# Identity + CA:
#   CA_ADDRESS                     - Istio CA
#                                     address
#                                     for cert
#                                     issuance
#   CA_ROOT_CA                     - CA root
#                                     CA cert
#                                     path
#   ALT_CA_HOSTNAME                - alternate
#                                     CA
#                                     hostname
#                                     for SNI
#   AUTH_TOKEN                     - SA token
#                                     path
#                                     (default
#                                     /var/run/
#                                     secrets/
#                                     tokens/
#                                     istio-token)
#   FAKE_CA                        - use fake
#                                     CA for
#                                     testing
#   SECRET_TTL                     - workload
#                                     cert TTL
#                                     duration
#   CRL_PATH                       - certificate
#                                     revocation
#                                     list path
#
# xDS (config from istiod):
#   XDS_ADDRESS                    - istiod xDS
#                                     server
#                                     address
#                                     (typically
#                                     istiod
#                                     .istio-
#                                     system.svc:
#                                     15012)
#   XDS_ROOT_CA                    - xDS root
#                                     CA cert
#                                     path
#   XDS_ON_DEMAND                  - lazy
#                                     workload
#                                     fetch
#   ALT_XDS_HOSTNAME               - alternate
#                                     xDS
#                                     hostname
#                                     for SNI
#   LOCAL_XDS_PATH                 - local xDS
#                                     file
#                                     path
#                                     (offline
#                                     mode)
#   LOCAL_XDS                      - inline xDS
#                                     config
#                                     YAML
#   XDS_HEADER_<name>              - custom
#                                     headers
#                                     for xDS
#                                     gRPC
#                                     (prefix
#                                     pattern)
#   CA_HEADER_<name>               - custom
#                                     headers
#                                     for CA
#                                     gRPC
#                                     (prefix
#                                     pattern)
#
# Kubernetes integration:
#   POD_NAME                       - this pod's
#                                     name
#                                     (downward
#                                     API)
#   POD_NAMESPACE                  - this pod's
#                                     namespace
#                                     (downward
#                                     API)
#   SERVICE_ACCOUNT                - SPIFFE
#                                     identity
#                                     (set by
#                                     k8s
#                                     ServiceAccount)
#   NODE_NAME                      - host node
#                                     name
#                                     (downward
#                                     API)
#   NETWORK                        - Istio
#                                     network
#                                     name
#                                     (multi-
#                                     network)
#   CLUSTER_ID                     - Istio
#                                     cluster
#                                     ID
#                                     (default
#                                     Kubernetes)
#   CLUSTER_DOMAIN                 - Kubernetes
#                                     cluster
#                                     domain
#                                     (default
#                                     cluster
#                                     .local)
#   PROXY_MODE                     - dedicated
#                                     or shared
#                                     (per-pod
#                                     vs per-
#                                     node
#                                     ztunnel)
#   PROXY_WORKLOAD_INFO            - per-pod
#                                     workload
#                                     info JSON
#
# In-pod CNI:
#   INPOD_UDS                      - in-pod CNI
#                                     UDS
#                                     socket
#                                     path
#                                     (where
#                                     CNI sends
#                                     pod-add/
#                                     pod-del
#                                     events)
#   INPOD_PORT_REUSE               - reuse
#                                     ports
#                                     across
#                                     pods
#   ENABLE_PROXY                   - enable
#                                     proxy
#                                     mode
#
# TCP keepalive (HBONE connection management):
#   KEEPALIVE_ENABLED              - enable TCP
#                                     keepalive
#   KEEPALIVE_TIME                 - TCP_
#                                     KEEPIDLE
#                                     seconds
#   KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL             - TCP_
#                                     KEEPINTVL
#                                     seconds
#   KEEPALIVE_RETRIES              - TCP_
#                                     KEEPCNT
#                                     count
#   USER_TIMEOUT_ENABLED           - TCP_USER_
#                                     TIMEOUT
#                                     enable
#
# Connection pool:
#   POOL_MAX_STREAMS_PER_CONNECTION - HTTP/2
#                                     pool max
#                                     streams
#                                     per conn
#   POOL_UNUSED_RELEASE_TIMEOUT    - pool
#                                     unused
#                                     release
#                                     timeout
#   CONNECTION_TERMINATION_DEADLINE - graceful
#                                     conn
#                                     termination
#                                     deadline
#   TERMINATION_GRACE_PERIOD_SECONDS - drain
#                                     timeout
#                                     for pod
#                                     termination
#
# Resource limits:
#   ZTUNNEL_WORKER_THREADS         - tokio
#                                     worker
#                                     thread
#                                     count
#                                     (default:
#                                     CPU
#                                     count)
#   ZTUNNEL_CPU_LIMIT              - CPU limit
#                                     (cgroup-
#                                     aware)
#   PACKET_MARK                    - SO_MARK
#                                     value for
#                                     egress
#                                     packets
#   ENABLE_ORIG_SRC                - use IP_
#                                     TRANSPARENT
#                                     (preserve
#                                     original
#                                     source IP)
#   AUTHZ_POLICY_INFO_LOGGING      - log
#                                     authorization
#                                     policy
#                                     decisions
#
# Metadata:
#   ISTIO_META_<name>              - workload
#                                     metadata
#                                     prefix
#                                     (per-
#                                     pod
#                                     custom
#                                     metadata)
#   PROXY_CONFIG                   - proxy
#                                     config
#                                     YAML
#                                     inline
#
# Build features (compile-time):
#   default                        - tls-aws-lc
#                                     (AWS-LC
#                                     FIPS-
#                                     capable
#                                     TLS)
#   tls-ring                       - rustls
#                                     with ring
#                                     TLS
#   tls-aws-lc                     - rustls
#                                     with
#                                     aws-lc-rs
#                                     TLS
#   tls-boring                     - rustls
#                                     with
#                                     BoringSSL
#                                     (Google's
#                                     OpenSSL
#                                     fork)
#   tls-openssl                    - rustls
#                                     with
#                                     OpenSSL
#   jemalloc                       - tikv-
#                                     jemallocator
#                                     allocator
#                                     (memory
#                                     profile-
#                                     friendly)
#   testing                        - rcgen
#                                     test cert
#                                     gen
#
# Example invocations:
#   # default proxy command
#   ztunnel
#
#   # explicit proxy command (same as default)
#   ztunnel proxy
#
#   # print version
#   ztunnel version
#
#   # In production: deployed as a DaemonSet on
#   # each Kubernetes node, with env vars
#   # projected by kubelet from the downward
#   # API + istiod's webhook injector.
#
# The prost lane is built on `prost = { version
# = "0.14", default-features = false }` +
# `prost-types = { version = "0.14",
# default-features = false }` + `tonic-prost =
# { version = "0.14", default-features = false
# }` + `tonic-prost-build = { version = "0.14",
# default-features = false }` (declared
# verbatim at upstream Cargo.toml HEAD as
# direct deps, imported by `src/proto.rs` +
# the xds + ca client modules for Protocol
# Buffers + gRPC wire encoding of:
#   - xDS protocol messages (envoy.config.* +
#     envoy.service.discovery.v3.*)
#   - Istio CA gRPC IstioCertificateService
#   - Workload + Authorization + Service
#     custom xDS resources (istio.workload.*)
#   - HBONE PROXY protocol metadata frames),
# the canonical Rust Protocol Buffers library
# by Tony Arcieri + Dan Burkert + Lucio Franco
# + the tokio-rs maintainers - github.com/
# tokio-rs/prost.
#
# tokio-rs/prost is the de-facto canonical Rust
# Protocol Buffers library:
#   - **Pure-Rust implementation** (no C++
#     protobuf library bindings; eliminates a
#     major C++ dep)
#   - **Build-time .proto compilation** (proto
#     files compiled to native Rust structs
#     via prost-build at cargo build time)
#   - **Serde integration** (optional;
#     generated structs can derive Serialize +
#     Deserialize)
#   - **No-std friendly** (default-features =
#     false makes it embedded-friendly)
#   - **tonic integration** (the canonical
#     Rust gRPC library [Axis 276 closer]
#     uses prost for protobuf wire encoding;
#     this is the canonical Rust gRPC stack)
#   - ~8,000 reverse-deps on crates.io
#   - 2,500+ stars on github.com/tokio-rs/prost
#
# prost's distinguishing position vs Rust
# protobuf alternatives:
#   - tokio-rs/prost (Arcieri + Burkert +
#     Franco + tokio-rs): canonical;
#     pure-Rust; tonic-paired; THIS AXIS
#   - rust-protobuf (stepancheg): older
#     pure-Rust protobuf; predates prost;
#     less actively maintained
#   - protobuf-codegen (paired with rust-
#     protobuf): code generator
#   - quick-protobuf: lightweight protobuf
#     without code-gen (manual encode/decode);
#     smaller binary size but less ergonomic
#
# The tokio-rs/prost team overlaps significantly
# with the tonic team (Lucio Franco is co-
# founder of both prost + tonic). This is the
# canonical *vertically-integrated Rust
# protocol stack*:
#   - tokio (async runtime)
#   - hyper (HTTP/1.1+HTTP/2)
#   - h2 (HTTP/2 primitive)
#   - tonic (gRPC client+server)
#   - prost (protobuf wire encoding)
#   - bytes (zero-copy byte buffer)
#   - tower (middleware composition)
# All maintained under the tokio-rs org.
#
# Tony Arcieri (the original prost author) is
# also the maintainer of RustCrypto (the
# canonical Rust cryptography ecosystem at
# github.com/RustCrypto). Arcieri's
# foundational-infrastructure footprint is
# substantial: prost (protobuf) + RustCrypto
# (crypto) + miscreant (misuse-resistant AEAD).
#
# Dan Burkert (prost co-maintainer) + Lucio
# Franco (tonic + prost co-author at
# hyperium/tokio-rs) round out the canonical
# Rust protocol stack maintainership.
#
# Multi-axis canonical-Rust author/org cohort
# extension (now spanning even more distinct
# authors):
#   - + Tony Arcieri + Dan Burkert + Lucio
#     Franco + tokio-rs org (tokio-rs/prost;
#     THIS AXIS; canonical Rust Protocol
#     Buffers + the vertically-integrated
#     gRPC stack culmination)
#
# Arcieri's joining the canonical-Rust cohort
# extends his *cryptography + protocol-
# infrastructure* presence. He is one of the
# very few individuals maintaining
# canonical-status libraries across both
# crypto (RustCrypto) AND protocol
# infrastructure (prost) verticals in Rust.
#
# ztunnel uses prost for:
#   - xDS gRPC client (`src/xds/`): receives
#     Workload + Service + Authorization
#     resources from istiod via xDS protocol
#   - CA gRPC client (`src/identity/`):
#     requests workload certificates from
#     istiod's IstioCertificateService
#   - HBONE PROXY metadata frames (`src/
#     proxy/`): encodes/decodes HBONE PROXY
#     protocol headers (source identity +
#     destination + traceID)
#
# This is the canonical use case for prost in
# a production data-plane: high-frequency
# protobuf encoding/decoding on the hot path
# (every xDS push + every cert refresh + every
# HBONE connection) where Rust's zero-copy
# bytes-based decoding via prost is critical
# for sub-ms latency at high pod-density
# (5,000+ workloads per cluster).
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 279 :: Protocol Buffers libraries
#              (binary serialization format
#              defined by Google's protobuf
#              spec at protobuf.dev/;
#              cross-language IDL-driven
#              codegen + zero-copy
#              wire encoding)
# Round 1535 :: Rust slot 1 of 4 :: OPENS Axis 279
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for
# this axis (proposed):
#   Rust    : tokio-rs/prost            - Arcieri +
#                                          Burkert +
#                                          Franco +
#                                          tokio-rs
#                                          maintainers
#                                          (pure-Rust
#                                          protobuf)
#   Go      : protocolbuffers/protobuf-go - Google's
#                                          official Go
#                                          protobuf
#                                          (google
#                                          .golang.org/
#                                          protobuf)
#   TS/Node : protobufjs/protobuf.js     - Daniel
#                                          Wirtz +
#                                          maintainers
#                                          (canonical
#                                          Node
#                                          protobuf)
#
# Protocol Buffers (protobuf) is the *most-
# deployed binary IDL* in production
# infrastructure:
#   - Originally developed at Google (2001);
#     open-sourced 2008
#   - Wire format spec at protobuf.dev
#   - Powers gRPC (Axis 276) wire encoding
#   - Used by Kubernetes API + etcd + most
#     CNCF projects
#   - Cross-language interop is the design
#     goal (same .proto file generates
#     idiomatic code for 10+ languages)
#
# Each canonical library provides:
#   - .proto file parser + code generator
#     (protoc plugin or build-time codegen)
#   - Generated message structs with idiomatic
#     language API
#   - Wire format encode/decode (protobuf
#     wire spec)
#   - Optional gRPC integration (protobuf is
#     the standard gRPC IDL)
#
# Protocol Buffers vs MessagePack (Axis 278):
#   - Protobuf: schema-defined (.proto file
#     required); strong typing; tag-based
#     wire format
#   - MessagePack: self-describing (no schema
#     needed); type-erased; type-prefix wire
#     format
#   - Different deployment patterns:
#     protobuf for stable APIs with versioned
#     schemas; msgpack for internal-format
#     dynamic data
#
# Axis 279 follows naturally from Axis 278
# (also binary serialization but with
# different design tradeoffs). Together
# Axes 278 + 279 cover the two dominant
# binary serialization landscapes in
# production polyglot systems.
#
# Use-case spectrum for this axis (so far):
#   - ztunnel (Rust, prost): Istio ambient
#     mesh xDS protocol + workload identity
#     gRPC + HBONE PROXY metadata
# ============================================================================

_ztunnel() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args
    local curcontext="$curcontext" ret=1

    _arguments -C \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]' \
        '1: :_ztunnel_cmds' \
        '*::arg:->args' \
    && ret=0

    return ret
}

_ztunnel_cmds() {
    local -a cmds
    cmds=(
        'proxy:start the ztunnel proxy (default if no command given)'
        'version:print version info (build hash + Istio version)'
        'help:print commands + version info'
    )
    _describe -t commands 'ztunnel command' cmds
}

_ztunnel "$@"
